    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Oct 15. 1877</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>It would be a great satisfaction to me to give you any information on the subject about which you write,—but I cannot do so. It seems incredible that mere contact should be poisonous, supposing the surface not to be abraided,<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Damon had mentioned accounts of fatalities caused by handling the sea snail <hi rend="italic">Conus geographus</hi>, and asked CD whether he could corroborate these reports (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11182.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Robert Damon, 12 October 1877</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
